tion where the body attacks the peripheral nerves, leading to rapid progression of weakness.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.019911,0.036287,0.053839,0.067194,0.085552,0.097785,0.10648,0.11594,0.11926,0.10839,0.09335,0.096003],"unified_progress":[0.023527,0.047025,0.069516,0.082806,0.092186,0.10802,0.10657,0.10849,0.10579,0.10165,0.085857,0.068561]},{"section":15,"text":"It's often preceded by a bacterial or viral infection, which fits her history.","dimension":0,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.036355,0.059694,0.070974,0.076582,0.083252,0.089898,0.097362,0.10177,0.10419,0.10475,0.092819,0.08235],"unified_progress":[0.0532,0.074689,0.077642,0.082359,0.087624,0.092994,0.093759,0.098313,0.094899,0.093338,0.081703,0.069481]},{"section":16,"text":"The CSF in GBS can have high protein but is usually not cloudy, which aligns with her presentation.","dimension":7,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.036597,0.053811,0.072176,0.081705,0.090774,0.095145,0.09718,0.097645,0.097524,0.094791,0.093137,0.089514],"unified_progress":[0.040278,0.062938,0.0769,0.084076,0.091473,0.094155,0.095033,0.096161,0.095595,0.094516,0.088837,0.080039]},{"section":17,"text":"Alternatively, it could be a variant like Miller Fisher syndrome, which is a form of GBS affecting the brainstem, but her symptoms here seem to involve the extremities more than the brainstem.","dimension":8,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.034321,0.046685,0.062589,0.073312,0.085305,0.094816,0.10031,0.10984,0.11291,0.10776,0.095569,0.076579],"unified_progress":[0.03614,0.058625,0.076625,0.088071,0.094252,0.10099,0.10103,0.1027,0.099504,0.096786,0.081899,0.063377]},{"section":18,"text":"Also, the radiculoneuropathy specifically mentions nerve root involvement, which is common in GBS affecting the nerve roots.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.040938,0.044008,0.060015,0.07228,0.084005,0.093051,0.099094,0.10452